    Don't touch `MicrosoftToDoIcon`, `authInit`, `runtimeConfig` here — those are DD tasks (050, 054, 055).

    --- Completion (Wave 7, 2026-06-18) ---

    Status: ✅ Completed.

    Shim location: `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/dailyBriefing.registration.ts` (79 lines; well under the ≤80 LOC ceiling; Calendar precedent is 62 lines).

    Factory location verified: `createDailyBriefingRegistration` lives in `@spaarke/ui-components` (NOT in `@spaarke/daily-briefing-components` — the new package only hoisted UI components + hooks + services; the registration factory remains in the shared lib's `WorkspaceShell/sections/dailyBriefing/`). Shim imports from `@spaarke/ui-components`.

    Shim shape (mirrors Calendar precedent):
      - Imports `createDailyBriefingRegistration` + `TELEMETRY_EVENT_DAILY_BRIEFING_429` + types from `@spaarke/ui-components`.
      - Imports LegalWorkspace-local `authenticatedFetch` + `getTenantId` from `../../services/authInit`.
      - Imports LegalWorkspace-local `trackEvent` from `../../services/telemetry`.
      - Exports `CreateLegalWorkspaceDailyBriefingRegistrationOptions` interface containing the optional `loadNotificationContext?: () => Promise<NarrateRequest | null>` (the P1 seam — FR-01 enabler).
      - Exports `createLegalWorkspaceDailyBriefingRegistration(options?)` factory wrapping the shared factory with LegalWorkspace-local auth + telemetry closures.
      - Default export `dailyBriefingRegistration: SectionRegistration` calls the factory with NO loader (standalone path — preserves the empty-payload contract; FR-25 / NFR-10 unchanged).
      - Re-exports `getTenantId` for future consumers / tests.

    `loadNotificationContext` threading evidence:
      `options.loadNotificationContext` (factory option) → `loadNotificationContext: options.loadNotificationContext` (forwarded to shared factory call) → shared factory pipes it to `DailyBriefingSection` props → `useDailyBriefing({ ..., loadNotificationContext })` → fetch envelope built from `loadNotificationContext()` return value. Fully plumbed end-to-end.

    Deleted (now-orphaned with the static const replaced):
      - `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/DailyBriefingSection.tsx` (101 LOC) — was the local wrapper that closed over auth + telemetry; that responsibility is now in the registration shim itself.
      - `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/useDailyBriefing.ts` (56 LOC) — local hook wrapper; replaced by direct usage of the shared hook inside the shared section component (no remaining LegalWorkspace consumers of the local hook).

    Build verification:
      - `npm run build` (Vite production) on `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` succeeds (3313 modules transformed; 13.31s). Same baseline as pre-task.
      - `npx tsc --noEmit` on `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` — zero `dailyBriefing`-related errors. Pre-existing TS6133 unused-import warnings in other shared lib files are unchanged baseline (NOT introduced by this task).
      - SpaarkeAi build failure on `@spaarke/sdap-client` resolution is PRE-EXISTING (verified by stash + rebuild at HEAD); independent of this task. Same baseline as `notes/task-002-blocker.md` captured.
      - Standalone DailyBriefing code page is owned by concurrent task 017 (Wave 7) — mid-flight; not verified here.

    Acceptance criteria check:
      ✅ Thin shim (79 lines ≤ 80; no business logic — only factory call + 6-line telemetry adapter).
      ✅ Shim consumes `createDailyBriefingRegistration` factory.
      ⏸️ SpaarkeAi cold-load real notifications — cannot verify in this task; requires task 002 (`main.tsx` wires the loader). This task UNBLOCKS that path.

